The six psutils binaries unconditionally `#include <unistd.h>` for
`getopt()`; MSVC doesn't ship `<unistd.h>`. Gate it on `!_WIN32` and
fall through to kpathsea's `<getopt.h>` on Windows, which already
provides a getopt replacement (kpathsea/getopt.c is in the kpathsea
lib's Windows srcs). Upstream's TL Windows build avoids this by
cross-compiling psutils with MinGW gcc instead of MSVC.

--- a/texk/psutils/psutils-src/epsffit.c
+++ b/texk/psutils/psutils-src/epsffit.c
@@ -17,7 +17,11 @@
 #include <stdlib.h>
 #include <string.h>
 #include <ctype.h>
+#ifdef _WIN32
+#include <kpathsea/getopt.h>
+#else
 #include <unistd.h>
+#endif
 #include "progname.h"
 #include "binary-io.h"
 

